00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:43.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sniper] Sniper Team 2, likewise.

137
00:07:44.063 --> 00:07:45.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chief] There's no point in resisting.

138
00:07:45.832 --> 00:07:48.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Give up and come quietly, Nagai.

139
00:07:48.067 --> 00:07:49.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't move!

140
00:07:50.002 --> 00:07:51.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So sorry, Grandma.

141
00:07:51.771 --> 00:07:53.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I don't mind at all.

142
00:07:53.639 --> 00:07:56.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kind of fun, like my police dramas on TV.

143
00:07:56.709 --> 00:07:59.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chuckles]
As long as I can escape like on TV.

144
00:08:02.682 --> 00:08:05.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't break the power poles! Stay inside!

145
00:08:09.655 --> 00:08:11.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up.

146
00:08:13.826 --> 00:08:15.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[officers grunting]

147
00:08:15.895 --> 00:08:16.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[officer] What's going on?

148
00:08:17.029 --> 00:08:17.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei] Okay.
-Huh?

149
00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:19.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] Take care of yourself, Grandma.

150
00:08:22.635 --> 00:08:24.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chief] Go! Get him!

151
00:08:33.713 --> 00:08:35.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Follow him. Don't let him get away.

152
00:08:42.088 --> 00:08:42.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

153
00:08:43.856 --> 00:08:46.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

154
00:08:51.831 --> 00:08:52.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

155
00:08:53.032 --> 00:08:55.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

156
00:08:57.603 --> 00:08:59.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[officer] Over here!
[chief] Shoot him!

157
00:09:01.240 --> 00:09:03.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunfire]

158
00:09:05.244 --> 00:09:06.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come out, ghost!

159
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:12.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it. I'm not ready yet.

160
00:09:17.290 --> 00:09:20.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll never let you catch me.
I'll never let you catch me.

161
00:09:20.326 --> 00:09:21.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll never-- [grunts]

162
00:09:34.674 --> 00:09:36.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chief] Where is he?

163
00:09:59.665 --> 00:10:01.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[officer] Damn it. Where did he go?

164
00:10:03.102 --> 00:10:05.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chief] He must have used that IBM thing.

165
00:10:06.105 --> 00:10:08.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Team 1 here. We lost the target.

166
00:10:08.374 --> 00:10:10.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Continue on with the search.

167
00:10:25.224 --> 00:10:26.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[helicopter whirring]

168
00:10:27.026 --> 00:10:28.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

169
00:10:31.297 --> 00:10:33.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it.

170
00:10:33.165 --> 00:10:37.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This whole mess.
Sato, it's all your fault.

171
00:10:38.938 --> 00:10:41.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm counting on you all. Let's get him.

172
00:10:43.943 --> 00:10:47.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki. The situation as it stands--

173
00:10:47.113 --> 00:10:48.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I heard the report over the radio.

174
00:10:49.048 --> 00:10:51.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What exactly are you planning to do next?

175
00:10:51.217 --> 00:10:53.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Araki] We're adding more people
to the search

176
00:10:53.419 --> 00:10:55.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and checking mainly around
where we lost track of Nagai.

177
00:10:55.988 --> 00:10:58.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then call them back at once.

178
00:10:58.257 --> 00:10:59.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Araki] Huh?

179
00:11:01.127 --> 00:11:02.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai is not an idiot.

180
00:11:03.062 --> 00:11:05.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure he's already familiar
with this area.

181
00:11:05.998 --> 00:11:09.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you try to chase him,
he'll just get away again.

182
00:11:09.201 --> 00:11:10.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Araki] Oh, right.

183
00:11:11.737 --> 00:11:14.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we do have him outnumbered.

184
00:11:14.940 --> 00:11:17.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We could do a clean sweep of the area.

185
00:11:19.078 --> 00:11:24.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we close in starting from here,
we're sure to catch him at some point.

186
00:11:25.451 --> 00:11:29.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but if the net is stretched too thin,
he could break through again.

187
00:11:29.822 --> 00:11:31.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No need to worry.

188
00:11:31.824 --> 00:11:34.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He can only use his IBM a few times a day.

189
00:11:34.960 --> 00:11:39.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From what I heard on the report,
Nagai has already used up his quota.

190
00:11:39.465 --> 00:11:42.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we use our numbers,
we'll surely catch him.

191
00:12:03.422 --> 00:12:04.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it.

192
00:12:05.724 --> 00:12:08.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What should I do? What should I do?

193
00:12:11.497 --> 00:12:13.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei] Are you looking for your cell phone?
-[gasps]

194
00:12:13.999 --> 00:12:14.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

195
00:12:17.203 --> 00:12:19.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei] <i>He said that the government</i>
<i>was after him.</i>

196
00:12:21.040 --> 00:12:24.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're gonna be of use to me, Nakano.

197
00:12:27.379 --> 00:12:28.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

198
00:12:30.416 --> 00:12:32.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

199
00:12:41.494 --> 00:12:42.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One more time.

200
00:12:43.062 --> 00:12:45.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

201
00:12:49.235 --> 00:12:50.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] What is it?

202
00:12:50.236 --> 00:12:52.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sokabe] Ko Nakano's cell phone
has been used,

203
00:12:52.171 --> 00:12:53.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and we've discovered his whereabouts.

204
00:12:53.806 --> 00:12:56.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Nakano? Take care of that yourself.</i>
<i>Kei Nagai--</i>

205
00:12:57.042 --> 00:12:59.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was used in the mountains,
near where you are.

206
00:12:59.945 --> 00:13:02.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki gasps]
The mountains where Nagai is hiding?

207
00:13:02.314 --> 00:13:04.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Yes. It can't be a coincidence.</i>

208
00:13:05.017 --> 00:13:06.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>They must be working together.</i>

209
00:13:06.352 --> 00:13:09.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Send me his exact location now.

210
00:13:11.056 --> 00:13:12.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes. Araki.

211
00:13:14.960 --> 00:13:15.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm on my way.

212
00:13:17.963 --> 00:13:19.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] He's dug his own grave.

213
00:13:20.065 --> 00:13:23.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe Nagai didn't realize
that we knew about Nakano.

214
00:13:26.805 --> 00:13:28.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

215
00:13:28.107 --> 00:13:29.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just...

216
00:13:30.843 --> 00:13:34.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There isn't a single sign in this place
that he had ever even been here.

217
00:13:35.881 --> 00:13:37.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This way. Hurry.

218
00:13:37.483 --> 00:13:39.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki]<i> He knew that this day would come.</i>

219
00:13:40.920 --> 00:13:45.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Someone as smart as he is</i>
<i>wouldn't make a rookie mistake like this.</i>

220
00:13:45.591 --> 00:13:47.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi]<i> So, then...?</i>

221
00:13:49.161 --> 00:13:52.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki]<i> Nagai is using Nakano</i>
<i>as a diversion...</i>

222
00:13:53.065 --> 00:13:55.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>so he can escape by himself.</i>

223
00:13:56.936 --> 00:13:58.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

224
00:14:08.447 --> 00:14:10.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're here. Surround it.

225
00:14:17.923 --> 00:14:20.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles] How do you like that?

226
00:14:20.492 --> 00:14:22.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I finally made it to the top.

227
00:14:24.330 --> 00:14:26.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh? It won't open.

228
00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:29.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it. [yells]

229
00:14:30.035 --> 00:14:31.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, go in.

230
00:14:33.339 --> 00:14:35.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

231
00:14:36.275 --> 00:14:37.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

232
00:14:43.415 --> 00:14:45.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't move. Put your hands...

233
00:14:47.052 --> 00:14:48.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

234
00:14:49.989 --> 00:14:51.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[reporter on phone]
<i>The southern part of Chiba</i>

235
00:14:51.924 --> 00:14:54.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>should expect south winds,</i>
<i>then later, easterly winds</i>

236
00:14:54.660 --> 00:14:57.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and clear skies followed by clouds.</i>

237
00:15:02.034 --> 00:15:04.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hurry!
I'm sure they'll have noticed by now.

238
00:15:04.169 --> 00:15:06.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If they surround us again, it's over!

239
00:15:06.205 --> 00:15:07.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then what are we gonna do?

240
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:11.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's risky,
but we'll have to take the shortest route.

241
00:15:13.279 --> 00:15:15.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's an escape point this way.

242
00:15:15.147 --> 00:15:17.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we can make it that far,
we're in the clear.

243
00:15:19.285 --> 00:15:20.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

244
00:15:21.553 --> 00:15:23.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ko grunting]

245
00:15:30.195 --> 00:15:31.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bit of a surprise?

246
00:15:31.697 --> 00:15:34.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thought you'd use Nakano as a diversion.

247
00:15:36.235 --> 00:15:38.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You might have escaped on your own
if you had.

248
00:15:39.038 --> 00:15:40.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's too bad.

249
00:15:42.608 --> 00:15:45.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll be sleeping
on the dissection table tonight,

250
00:15:45.544 --> 00:15:47.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
003...

251
00:15:48.514 --> 00:15:49.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei Nagai.

252
00:15:50.582 --> 00:15:51.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

253
00:15:58.424 --> 00:16:00.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it.

254
00:16:00.326 --> 00:16:03.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why... me?

255
00:16:06.432 --> 00:16:07.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting in muffled voice]

256
00:16:10.369 --> 00:16:11.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why me?

257
00:16:11.603 --> 00:16:13.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] Okay, take him.

258
00:16:13.339 --> 00:16:15.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no need to worry about his IBM.

259
00:16:18.143 --> 00:16:22.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn... you.

260
00:16:28.587 --> 00:16:30.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn you.

261
00:16:30.389 --> 00:16:32.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

262
00:16:39.765 --> 00:16:42.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No!

263
00:16:42.534 --> 00:16:44.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all gasp]

264
00:16:44.203 --> 00:16:45.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wha--?

265
00:16:48.707 --> 00:16:50.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wha--? What's this?

266
00:16:50.609 --> 00:16:52.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
His IBM is...

267
00:16:56.215 --> 00:16:57.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[officer 1] Shields.
[officer 2] Look out.

268
00:16:57.483 --> 00:16:59.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[officers grunting]

269
00:16:59.318 --> 00:17:00.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand back.

270
00:17:16.668 --> 00:17:18.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is completely insane.

271
00:17:25.177 --> 00:17:28.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki, get back. [gasps]

272
00:17:30.049 --> 00:17:31.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If putting him to sleep won't stop it...

273
00:17:31.683 --> 00:17:33.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] Mr. Tosaki. [screams]

274
00:17:39.792 --> 00:17:41.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
...then I just have to kill him.

275
00:17:44.830 --> 00:17:47.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] <i>Is it not Nagai's?</i>

276
00:17:49.435 --> 00:17:52.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>No. Even killing him won't stop it.</i>

277
00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:55.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[IBM] Serves you right.

278
00:17:56.275 --> 00:17:58.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] Mr. Tosaki!

279
